from killing you

22:20.607 --> 22:23.009
when all's said and done,
do you remember your answer?

22:23.109 --> 22:25.812
No, but I'm guessing
you do.

22:25.912 --> 22:28.581
I believe you said,

22:28.681 --> 22:31.083
"We might be friends
by then."

22:31.183 --> 22:32.619
( snickers )

22:32.719 --> 22:35.822
I'm sorry,
what are you driving at?

22:35.922 --> 22:37.890
You've spent enough time
with the man now.

22:37.990 --> 22:39.759
Does he strike you
as the type of person

22:39.859 --> 22:41.861
who would ever
under any circumstance

22:41.961 --> 22:43.830
leave a loose end
like you walking around?

22:46.198 --> 22:48.768
When I took your advice
and lifted the ban
on Charles Vane,

22:48.868 --> 22:52.405
I became the center
of all commerce on this
island again.

22:52.505 --> 22:54.907
Someone you don't want
as an enemy.

22:55.007 --> 22:58.244
Someone Flint doesn't
want as an enemy.

22:58.344 --> 23:02.449
The way I see it,
I may be the only person
in this world

23:02.549 --> 23:04.884
who can dissuade him
from killing you.

23:10.557 --> 23:12.391
Miranda:
I had a very
different life

23:12.492 --> 23:15.194
before I came here,

23:15.294 --> 23:17.664
a life I shared
with my husband.

23:19.432 --> 23:22.435
He was a special man,

23:22.535 --> 23:24.537
a man of ideas...

23:24.637 --> 23:26.573
about the world,

23:26.673 --> 23:28.641
about the order
of things.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.779
Writers, artists,
men of science--

23:32.879 --> 23:35.915
they'd fill our drawing room
night after night

23:36.015 --> 23:38.518
to talk and argue.

23:39.886 --> 23:42.622
Sometimes just
to listen to him.

23:44.557 --> 23:46.626
In some ways
he was like you--

23:46.726 --> 23:49.061
a shepherd
to his flock.

23:50.497 --> 23:52.632
He would have loved
to have met you.

23:54.000 --> 23:55.535
Me?

23:55.635 --> 23:57.704
You think I can play
devil's advocate.

23:57.804 --> 23:59.572
Thomas would have played
that game with you

23:59.672 --> 24:01.674
from dusk until dawn.

24:01.774 --> 24:03.943
And everything
you hold sacred,

24:04.043 --> 24:06.245
he'd leave in tatters.

24:06.345 --> 24:08.948
Not from malice or hate,

24:09.048 --> 24:11.651
but from love.

24:11.751 --> 24:14.621
From a desire to see
the yoke of shame

24:14.721 --> 24:16.923
lifted from your shoulders.

24:18.290 --> 24:20.660
You think I am ashamed?

24:22.729 --> 24:24.831
My husband
and I were happy.

24:26.533 --> 24:28.568
But in London,
a happy life

24:28.668 --> 24:30.603
can often be
a very dangerous thing.

24:32.071 --> 24:35.107
Something that other people
simply cannot abide.

24:37.977 --> 24:40.747
Thomas learned
that lesson all too well.

24:43.916 --> 24:47.119
Captain Flint was
Thomas's closest friend.

24:48.354 --> 24:50.022
And after his death,
he saw fit

24:50.122 --> 24:53.693
to spirit me here
for my own safety.

24:53.793 --> 24:55.862
Flint brought you here?

24:57.096 --> 24:58.798
You're right,
I don't understand.

24:58.898 --> 25:02.001
I just told you.
Captain Flint is
my deliverer.

25:02.101 --> 25:05.204
There's nothing more
you need to understand.

25:08.107 --> 25:10.276
Why are you here?

25:12.444 --> 25:14.213
I'm concerned
for your safety.

25:14.313 --> 25:15.915
It's late.

25:16.015 --> 25:18.685
You knew I'd be alone.
It's inappropriate.

25:22.354 --> 25:25.892
You're not here
because you want to
protect me, Pastor.

25:27.493 --> 25:29.896
You're here because
you want to fuck me.

26:08.167 --> 26:11.137
( moans )

26:14.874 --> 26:17.644
( breathing heavily )

26:32.625 --> 26:35.361
I'm sorry.
We dangle?

26:36.629 --> 26:39.365
Four men suspended
over the side.

26:39.465 --> 26:42.034
Axes, augers, charges.

26:42.134 --> 26:44.904
It's a rapid penetration
to get a charge through
the hole.

26:45.004 --> 26:48.641
Cause disruption,
distraction

26:48.741 --> 26:52.244
while we move on the bunker
through the hold below.

26:52.344 --> 26:53.545
Saw Avery try it once.

26:53.646 --> 26:56.615
- And it worked?
- I said I saw it tried.

26:58.050 --> 27:00.319
Volunteers?

27:08.260 --> 27:10.196
( sighs )

27:10.296 --> 27:12.732
Paxton.

27:14.333 --> 27:16.202
Bobby.

27:18.437 --> 27:20.339
Dooly.

27:23.309 --> 27:24.711
Logan.

27:30.449 --> 27:31.918
Something wrong?

27:32.018 --> 27:34.586
Even if we do
hack through,

27:34.687 --> 27:37.023
we'd be dangling there
like bait on a string.

27:37.123 --> 27:38.958
It's suicide.

27:39.058 --> 27:42.594
We don't have time
for a debate, Mr. Logan.

27:42.695 --> 27:44.964
Now I gave you an order.

27:45.064 --> 27:48.400
And what happens when
those orders get us killed?

27:48.500 --> 27:51.037
You send in four more?

27:51.137 --> 27:53.773
Billy, tell him
I'm right.

28:01.748 --> 28:03.215
Mr. Logan...

28:05.317 --> 28:07.686
fall in.

28:07.787 --> 28:09.722
Billy, tell him
I'm right.

28:12.558 --> 28:13.793
Captain--

28:13.893 --> 28:17.329
Mr. Logan makes
a valid point.

28:20.199 --> 28:23.602
Unfortunately,
now is not the time.

28:23.702 --> 28:26.372
( crew gasps )

28:28.975 --> 28:30.777
Anybody else
got a point

28:30.877 --> 28:33.645
they would
like to make?

28:33.746 --> 28:35.381
While we are in battle,

28:35.481 --> 28:36.983
the captain's orders
are the law.

28:37.083 --> 28:39.251
That is what
we signed up to.

28:39.351 --> 28:41.420
That is what we agreed.

28:43.956 --> 28:46.492
Now the order's
been given.

28:46.592 --> 28:48.194
Heed it!

28:54.834 --> 28:57.536
( man whistles )

28:57.636 --> 28:59.872
Man:
Captain!

29:17.123 --> 29:18.958
I can't believe
I didn't see it before.

29:19.058 --> 29:21.527
It was staring us
right in the face.

29:21.627 --> 29:25.264
Those cannons aren't
the only thing Bryson has
locked down there with him.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.169
38 slaves.

29:30.269 --> 29:33.739
You think they put that flag
there as a signal to us?

29:33.840 --> 29:35.507
Well, it wasn't there
three hours ago.

29:35.607 --> 29:37.910
And if not us, I couldn't
tell you who they are
trying to signal.

29:38.010 --> 29:39.979
Seven, eight...

29:40.079 --> 29:42.348
nine priced over £100.

29:42.448 --> 29:45.384
That's nine strong men
ready to fight Bryson
from below.

29:45.484 --> 29:48.054
Yeah, well, you're presuming
those nine men

29:48.154 --> 29:50.189
will choose to take up arms
and join in a fight

29:50.289 --> 29:52.825
they couldn't possibly know
or care less about.

29:52.925 --> 29:54.493
Given their
current situation,

29:54.593 --> 29:56.963
my presumption
is that there are no
nine men on earth

29:57.063 --> 29:59.465
who wouldn't jump
at the chance for
a little fight.

29:59.565 --> 30:02.869
What, you got
a better idea?

30:04.570 --> 30:07.206
Well, how do you imagine we get
them out of their chains?

30:16.883 --> 30:19.085
Woman:
You will never
see them again.

30:19.185 --> 30:21.287
What?

30:22.889 --> 30:25.124
This person you'd give
your life to protect,

30:25.224 --> 30:28.227
give our lives
to protect...

30:30.062 --> 30:32.764
whoever they are,
you'll never see them again.

30:32.865 --> 30:35.501
You must love them
very much,

30:35.601 --> 30:37.636
but I do not think you
have thought this through.

30:37.736 --> 30:39.371
You don't know me.

30:39.471 --> 30:42.208
And you don't know
what you're talking about.

30:42.308 --> 30:44.843
I know that if we reach
our destination,

30:44.944 --> 30:46.845
we may never have another
chance like this.

30:46.946 --> 30:48.614
There is no way.

30:50.449 --> 30:53.886
You and I,
we are both in this hold,

30:53.986 --> 30:56.488
but we are not
in the same place.

30:58.590 --> 31:01.027
How many times must you
have told yourself

31:01.127 --> 31:03.462
that you're special?

31:03.562 --> 31:07.433
That your master
thinks you're different
from the rest?

31:08.734 --> 31:10.269
Maybe you're right.

31:10.369 --> 31:12.804
But I know those men above
better than you.

31:12.905 --> 31:15.574
And when they put you
in these,

31:15.674 --> 31:18.210
they don't mean
to let you go.

31:21.047 --> 31:22.681
You have a chance
to go home again,

31:22.781 --> 31:24.450
yet you just sit there.

31:26.152 --> 31:28.020
Maybe you're right.

31:29.355 --> 31:31.958
You and I
are not the same.

31:41.600 --> 31:43.002
( thumps )

31:47.974 --> 31:50.276
( clanks )

31:52.044 --> 31:54.146
( hisses )

32:04.823 --> 32:07.326
( door opens )

32:10.296 --> 32:12.965
What the fuck
is going on down here?

32:26.445 --> 32:28.847
Sir.

32:28.947 --> 32:30.549
It's this one.

32:49.701 --> 32:52.138
( choking )

33:15.727 --> 33:19.065
( panting )

33:26.372 --> 33:29.241
( rhythmic thudding )

33:31.943 --> 33:34.280
Men:
Heave!

33:34.380 --> 33:37.383
- Man: Together, lads.
And...
- Heave.

33:38.384 --> 33:40.819
What do they think
they're doing?

33:40.919 --> 33:43.522
( thudding continues )

33:52.464 --> 33:53.532
Come.

33:59.037 --> 34:01.707
- Heave!
- Man: Again!

34:03.675 --> 34:05.677
- ( clangs )
- Heave!

34:14.753 --> 34:16.487
Put your back in it, boys!

34:17.656 --> 34:20.126
( rhythmic thudding
continues )

34:29.301 --> 34:32.070
Secure the hold, Mr. Hayes.
Something's wrong.

34:32.170 --> 34:34.106
( whistles )

34:40.646 --> 34:42.714
( shouting )

34:49.054 --> 34:51.190
( gunshots )

35:13.011 --> 35:14.613
- ( gunshot )
- ( groans )

35:18.917 --> 35:21.220
( shouting )

35:22.221 --> 35:24.390
( grunting )

35:33.599 --> 35:35.434
( grunts )

35:45.811 --> 35:47.213
( shouts )

36:15.341 --> 36:17.409
( urinating )

36:21.347 --> 36:24.950
Excuse me.
Mr. Hamund?

36:25.050 --> 36:26.385
Who the fuck are you?

36:26.485 --> 36:29.288
My name is John Silver.

36:29.388 --> 36:31.323
And I have
a proposition for you.

36:31.423 --> 36:33.191
I've heard your crew has
been freed to hunt again.

36:33.292 --> 36:35.026
And I understand with
Mr. Rackham out of favor,

36:35.126 --> 36:36.628
you're the man the crew
now looks to.

36:39.398 --> 36:41.667
Seems our paths were meant
to meet in this moment.

36:41.767 --> 36:44.670
Me with something to sell,
and you with means to use it.

36:44.770 --> 36:46.938
Piss off.

36:50.075 --> 36:52.544
I was the whore's partner,

36:52.644 --> 36:54.680
the one who stole
the page from Flint

36:54.780 --> 36:57.215
and then tried
to sell it to you.

36:57.316 --> 36:59.685
You're that new one.

36:59.785 --> 37:02.153
- The cook they took on.
- That I am.

37:02.254 --> 37:03.589
But perhaps not for long.

37:03.689 --> 37:05.857
This is where I think you
and I can help each other.

37:07.993 --> 37:11.630
The night the exchange
was meant to take place
at the wrecks,

37:11.730 --> 37:13.965
I lost the schedule
to Captain Flint.

37:14.065 --> 37:16.735
But I escaped
with my hide intact

37:16.835 --> 37:18.504
and my anonymity.

37:18.604 --> 37:20.238
I've remained
with the crew since then,

37:20.339 --> 37:23.108
but I believe now
I've tempted fate
long enough.

37:23.208 --> 37:25.110
Flint departed,
I remained.

37:25.210 --> 37:26.945
My intent--
to sell the page again

37:27.045 --> 37:29.648
and leave Nassau with
something to show for it.

37:29.748 --> 37:32.351
Seeing as we theoretically
already had a deal,

37:32.451 --> 37:34.886
I thought your crew was
the logical place to start.

37:36.322 --> 37:38.324
What the fuck
are you talking about?

37:38.424 --> 37:40.392
You just said Flint
has the schedule.

37:40.492 --> 37:43.261
He has the page
the schedule is written on,

37:43.362 --> 37:45.531
but I saw that page.

37:45.631 --> 37:48.133
I think there's a good chance
I can remember most of it.

37:48.233 --> 37:49.868
For the right price.

37:49.968 --> 37:52.404
Are you a fucking lunatic?

37:52.504 --> 37:54.340
What's to stop me
from killing you

37:54.440 --> 37:56.141
for getting us
into this mess?

37:56.241 --> 37:57.876
Wait.

37:57.976 --> 38:00.546
I am willing to give
a steep discount on our
original agreement.

38:00.646 --> 38:04.616
We don't have any fucking
money left, you shit.

38:04.716 --> 38:07.886
Rackham lost it
chasing you.

38:09.355 --> 38:11.957
I fail to see
how that's possible.

38:20.165 --> 38:23.301
Mr. Hamund.
May I help you?

38:23.402 --> 38:26.805
You told us you lost
our pearls in the wrecks.

38:26.905 --> 38:30.175
5,000 pesos worth.
Isn't that right?

38:30.275 --> 38:31.877
Yes.

38:31.977 --> 38:35.481
Because now I'm told
that you gave half our pearls

38:35.581 --> 38:37.449
to the whore up front

38:37.549 --> 38:40.419
before you ever
left for the wrecks.

38:45.757 --> 38:50.095
Which would mean
that half the pearls
never went to the wrecks.

38:53.198 --> 38:56.768
They was on the whore
when your bitch reeled her in.

38:58.504 --> 39:01.373
Leaving us to wonder

39:01.473 --> 39:03.542
where the fuck
are they now?

39:06.044 --> 39:08.313
I don't know where you're
getting your information from,

39:08.414 --> 39:09.781
but I can assure you,
it is mistaken.

39:09.881 --> 39:12.217
She threw that whore
in the tent

39:12.317 --> 39:14.453
long before we got to her.

39:14.553 --> 39:16.788
Yes, but the whore
had no pearls.

39:16.888 --> 39:20.191
Neither I nor Miss Bonny
would be so stupid as to
steal from you.

39:20.291 --> 39:22.861
And even if I were, I would
certainly never be so stupid

39:22.961 --> 39:24.863
as to trust a whore
to act as escrow.

39:24.963 --> 39:27.198
Someone is lying to you.

39:27.298 --> 39:30.402
If you tell me who it was,
I might be able to help you
figure out why.

39:32.337 --> 39:35.240
I'd tell you, Jack...

39:35.340 --> 39:38.209
but I don't see
how that much matters

39:38.309 --> 39:41.046
seeing that we found these

39:41.146 --> 39:44.015
in your tent just now.

39:46.317 --> 39:49.154
Look at you now.

39:50.722 --> 39:53.158
Where's the fucking
rest of them?

39:54.292 --> 39:56.762
Buried.

39:56.862 --> 39:58.497
By the wrecks.

40:00.231 --> 40:02.601
Darling.

40:02.701 --> 40:04.936
I'm so very
disappointed in you.

40:25.457 --> 40:27.793
I believe
I'm entitled to this.

40:33.499 --> 40:36.034
I've arranged
a room for you.

40:36.134 --> 40:38.136
I don't imagine I'll be
doing much sleeping

40:38.236 --> 40:41.439
till I know this is finished,
thank you very much.

40:41.540 --> 40:43.842
Thought I'd wait it out here,
if you don't mind.

40:51.082 --> 40:52.951
- Men: Heave ho!
- Pull!

40:53.051 --> 40:55.654
Come on!
That's it!

40:55.754 --> 40:57.989
Heave!

40:58.089 --> 41:00.191
Man:
All right, lads,
coming over.

41:00.291 --> 41:01.693
Man #2:
Coming over.

41:01.793 --> 41:03.261
Man #3:
Okay, that's good.

41:03.361 --> 41:06.164
( shouting continues )

41:09.735 --> 41:12.671
I certainly didn't expect
to find you down in the hold.

41:14.039 --> 41:17.208
Not after you betrayed
Miss Guthrie on behalf
of her father.

41:20.145 --> 41:24.115
Our agreement was I would
stay behind to protect
Eleanor from you.

41:24.215 --> 41:26.084
( scoffs )

41:26.184 --> 41:29.320
You think what
she and I hope to achieve

41:29.420 --> 41:31.857
for Nassau is impossible.

41:31.957 --> 41:33.825
That I'll be
the death of her?

41:40.065 --> 41:43.034
I lost six men
chasing down this ship.

41:43.134 --> 41:45.971
Nearly faced another mutiny
all over again.

41:47.839 --> 41:50.308
If I had any sense,
I'd throw you to my crew.

41:50.408 --> 41:53.011
Take the pressure off me.

41:55.146 --> 41:56.281
But I'm not gonna do that.

41:59.818 --> 42:01.820
I'd rather prove you wrong.

42:24.509 --> 42:25.977
Billy.

42:28.546 --> 42:29.915
Stow the guns
in the lower hold.

42:30.015 --> 42:32.517
- Favor the starboard.
- Of course.

42:32.618 --> 42:34.686
Right, Billy.

42:38.890 --> 42:41.927
What?
Afraid I got loose lips?

42:45.363 --> 42:47.532
Please, son,
I am on your side.

42:47.633 --> 42:49.567
You've got to believe that.

42:49.668 --> 42:52.604
Then get some answers.

42:58.043 --> 43:00.278
Man:
Come on!

43:00.378 --> 43:03.481
- Heave!
- Crew: Heave ho.

43:03.581 --> 43:06.217
That's it.
Hold on.

43:09.855 --> 43:11.089
Lend a hand, mate.

43:11.189 --> 43:13.024
Perfectly good
stash of powder here.

43:16.027 --> 43:17.829
( screams )

43:23.268 --> 43:25.303
- ( men shouting, screaming )
- ( coughs )

43:29.174 --> 43:31.242
You all right?

43:36.014 --> 43:37.548
She saw us.

43:37.649 --> 43:39.985
The Scarborough
had to have seen us.

43:42.220 --> 43:44.389
There's still
great guns in the hold.

43:44.489 --> 43:46.391
At least three
or four more.

43:46.491 --> 43:48.326
There's no time
for delay.

43:48.426 --> 43:50.862
The guns we've unloaded
already will have to suffice.

43:50.962 --> 43:53.665
Cut us loose!
We're getting out of here.

43:53.765 --> 43:56.201
( men shouting )

44:07.713 --> 44:09.314
Man:
Come on!

44:23.561 --> 44:25.430
What the hell is that?

44:26.965 --> 44:29.167
It's the Andromache's
spritsail brace.

44:29.267 --> 44:31.069
It must have blown loose
during the explosion.

44:31.169 --> 44:33.905
That's two knots or more
it'll drag us down.

44:53.792 --> 44:57.562
Earlier...

44:57.662 --> 44:59.765
when you and Mr. Gates
were having words,

44:59.865 --> 45:02.000
you mentioned a letter.

45:04.669 --> 45:06.204
What was in it, Billy?

45:16.547 --> 45:18.616
Billy!

45:18.716 --> 45:20.485
What was in it?

45:23.922 --> 45:27.192
I think you know
what was in it.

45:28.760 --> 45:31.029
( cannon fire )

45:32.330 --> 45:33.899
Oh, shit!

45:36.734 --> 45:40.471
( men shouting,
screaming )

45:40.571 --> 45:42.974
Hard to starboard.
Bring us about.

45:48.579 --> 45:50.748
Man overboard!

45:50.849 --> 45:54.385
Man:
Man overboard!

45:56.054 --> 45:58.957
It's Billy.
He fell.

46:00.691 --> 46:03.128
- Billy!
- Billy!

46:03.228 --> 46:05.130
Any sign of him?

46:13.872 --> 46:15.841
We can't turn back.

46:20.545 --> 46:22.881
She'll tear us to pieces.

46:50.942 --> 46:52.377
Ambush, I presume.

46:52.477 --> 46:56.147
Nothing out there but men
with pistols and swords.

46:56.247 --> 46:59.117
I imagine those pearls
didn't just materialize
out of thin air.

46:59.217 --> 47:00.818
With whom did you
scheme this?

47:00.919 --> 47:02.653
The cunt.

47:02.753 --> 47:04.422
( scoffs )

47:04.522 --> 47:06.824
Somehow I'm not surprised.

47:08.894 --> 47:10.761
Decent fellow, Slade,
as far as I know.

47:10.862 --> 47:12.630
Never raised a hand
against the whore.

47:12.730 --> 47:15.133
A factor I hope
you considered before
you decided that he

47:15.233 --> 47:17.802
and six other men
who stood by our captain
in his darkest hour,

47:17.903 --> 47:19.704
men he considers
his brothers,

47:19.804 --> 47:23.074
be lumped into the cost
of assuaging your offense
in this matter.

47:24.375 --> 47:26.044
God damn it, Anne.

47:26.144 --> 47:28.346
Do I not deserve
a say about this?

47:30.381 --> 47:32.450
You had your say.

47:32.550 --> 47:34.552
Now I'll have mine.

47:52.670 --> 47:54.940
This way.

48:07.752 --> 48:10.021
( bird screeching )

48:22.100 --> 48:24.535
You know,
when I first met you,

48:24.635 --> 48:27.205
I pegged you
for an easy mark.

48:28.839 --> 48:31.142
But now,
between you and Flint,

48:31.242 --> 48:33.411
I'm not certain who
I should be more afraid of.

48:38.716 --> 48:40.651
I saw you earlier.

48:40.751 --> 48:42.988
After you lifted the ban.

48:46.391 --> 48:49.961
( chuckles )
You were angry.

48:50.962 --> 48:53.164
Not just about Max.

48:55.800 --> 48:57.935
Those men out there,

48:58.036 --> 49:00.038
they made you admit
you were wrong.

49:01.072 --> 49:02.307
They made you feel weak.

49:06.611 --> 49:08.913
I think you felt compelled

49:09.014 --> 49:11.682
to let everyone
on this island know

49:11.782 --> 49:14.952
that in this place,

49:15.053 --> 49:18.556
no one fucks with you
and gets away with it.

49:18.656 --> 49:21.392
( screams )

49:28.833 --> 49:31.202
( groaning )

49:34.639 --> 49:37.208
( panting )

49:40.045 --> 49:41.179
( knocks )

49:50.455 --> 49:52.757
( door closes )

50:17.982 --> 50:19.917
Thank you

50:20.017 --> 50:22.287
for what you did for me.

50:28.893 --> 50:31.229
I didn't do it for you.

51:15.740 --> 51:18.243
Dufresne:
Old Jim Carver.

51:26.751 --> 51:29.287
Sebastian Frakes.

51:39.330 --> 51:42.367
William "Bones" Manderly.

51:43.834 --> 51:44.869
Men:
Huzzah!

52:22.039 --> 52:23.708
I hope you're pleased
with yourself.

52:26.911 --> 52:29.347
I see. We won't be speaking
of this again, I presume.

52:30.981 --> 52:33.518
Well, before we close
the lid on this and put
it in the ground,

52:33.618 --> 52:35.253
one last question
if you will,

52:35.353 --> 52:37.222
just to satisfy
my curiosity.

52:40.591 --> 52:43.027
When you
and Miss Guthrie were
plotting this little coup,

52:43.127 --> 52:45.663
when she asked you,
"Well, shit, Anne,

52:45.763 --> 52:48.132
what makes you think
old Jack will go along
with this plan of ours

52:48.233 --> 52:49.567
and not plead
the truth to his men

52:49.667 --> 52:52.203
as he's most certainly going
to feel duty-bound to do?"

52:52.303 --> 52:55.273
What did you say?

52:55.373 --> 52:58.409
I told her given the choice
between them and me...

53:00.177 --> 53:01.612
you'd choose me.

53:03.381 --> 53:05.250
That's very
fucking touching.

53:08.319 --> 53:09.754
And the captain?

53:09.854 --> 53:12.156
The two of you come up
with some idea how
to deal with him

53:12.257 --> 53:13.958
when he returns and finds out
about all this?

53:16.126 --> 53:18.796
You don't know
where he's gone, do you?

53:23.200 --> 53:24.835
He ain't coming back.

54:09.079 --> 54:12.249
( instrumental music
playing )
